height%3D%5C%22957%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Pascale%20Duguay.%3Cp%3ENiall%20Lowe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAs%20a%20child%2C%20my%20grandmother%20used%20to%20give%20my%20sister%20and%20me%20a%20quarter%20when%20she%20came%20to%20visit.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOnce%2C%20she%20forgot%2C%20so%20I%20pointed%20it%20out.%20My%20mother%20was%20so%20mortified%20she%20sent%20me%20to%20my%20room.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThat%20rebuke%20unconsciously%20taught%20me%20I%20shouldn't%20ask%20for%20money%2C%20and%20it%20held%20me%20back%20for%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20have%20many%20memories%20of%20my%20maternal%20grandmother%20as%20she%20passed%20away%20when%20I%20was%204%20years%20old.%20One%20incident%20stuck%20in%20my%20mind%20very%20clearly%2C%20however%2C%20and%20surprisingly%2C%20only%20decades%20later%20did%20I%20realize%20that%20it%20had%20shaped%20the%20way%20I'd%20been%20managing%20my%20finances%20all%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20time%20my%20grandmother%20dropped%20by%20for%20a%20visit%2C%20she'd%20give%20my%20sister%20and%20me%20a%20quarter%2C%20which%20we%20happily%20added%20to%20our%20piggy%20bank.%20One%20day%2C%20she%20forgot%20to%20do%20so%2C%20and%20when%20I%20pointed%20this%20out%20to%20her%2C%20she%20immediately%20dug%20into%20her%20purse%20to%20rectify%20the%20matter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mother%2C%20utterly%20mortified%2C%20sent%20me%20to%20my%20room%20with%20the%20stern%20admonishment%20that%20asking%20for%20money%20was%20not%20polite.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20didn't%20see%20what%20the%20big%20deal%20was.%20Why%20couldn't%20I%20ask%20for%20money%3F%20After%20all%2C%20I%20asked%20for%20plenty%20of%20other%20stuff%20all%20the%20time%2C%20like%20extra%20dessert%20helpings%20and%20bedtime%20stories.%20What%20was%20so%20wrong%20about%20asking%20for%20money%3F%20My%20mom%20never%20did%20explain%2C%20and%2C%20although%20well-intentioned%2C%20the%20rebuke%20stayed%20with%20me%2C%20unconsciously%20affecting%20my%20finances.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20felt%20uncomfortable%20asking%20for%20what%20I%20needed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20it%20limited%20my%20earning%20potential%20as%20it%20stopped%20me%20from%20asking%20for%20more.%20It%20was%20easier%20for%20me%20to%20quietly%20accept%20what%20was%20being%20offered%2C%20especially%20when%20interviewing%20for%20a%20new%20job%2C%20than%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20offer%20seems%20a%20bit%20low.%20Can%20you%20raise%20it%20to%20X%20amount%20instead%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20only%20learned%20this%20trick%20much%20later%20when%20I%20was%20well%20into%20my%20freelance%20writing%20career.%20It%20didn't%20come%20easily%20(it%20still%20doesn't%2C%20by%20the%20way)%2C%20but%20I've%20learned%20that%20it%20is%20actually%20expected%20of%20me.%20Not%20only%20does%20it%20make%20me%20look%20like%20a%20professional%2C%20but%20it%20makes%20me%20feel%20like%20one%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20incident%20also%20affected%20my%20ability%20to%20ask%20for%20financial%20help%2C%20whether%20small%20sums%20for%20minor%20projects%20or%20larger%20ones%20for%20big-time%20items%20like%20an%20auto%20loan%20or%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%3Emortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20loan.%20In%20every%20instance%2C%20I%20kept%20feeling%20as%20if%20I%20had%20to%20do%20it%20all%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20did%20slow%20my%20progress%2C%20it%20helped%20me%20see%20the%20value%20of%20putting%20money%20aside%20so%20that%20I'd%20eventually%20be%20able%20to%20reach%20my%20goals.%20Another%20valuable%20side%20effect%20is%20that%20it%20built%20my%20perseverance%20muscles%20to%20Ms.%20Olympia%20levels%20%E2%80%94%20a%20truly%20helpful%20trait%20when%20freelancing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAccepting%20money%20was%20just%20as%20hard%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20moolah%20did%20show%20up%2C%20another%20host%20of%20issues%20arose.%20I%20found%20it%20was%20as%20difficult%20to%20accept%20money%20as%20it%20was%20to%20ask%20for%20it%2C%20especially%20if%20it%20happened%20to%20be%20a%20gift.%20After%20all%2C%20I%20hadn't%20worked%20for%20it%2C%20so%20how%20could%20I%20possibly%20deserve%20this%20bonus%3F%20It's%20as%20if%20the%20little%20girl%20inside%20me%20kept%20looking%20over%20her%20shoulder%20to%20see%20if%20anyone%20would%20send%20her%20back%20to%20her%20room%20pronto%20for%20daring%20to%20reach%20out%20and%20take%20what%20was%20being%20offered.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20strange%20questions%20would%20pop%20up%20in%20my%20mind%3A%20Was%20I%20being%20pitied%3F%20Were%20people%20feeling%20sorry%20for%20me%3F%20No%20doubt%20a%20remnant%20from%20flashbacks%20of%20my%20grandmother%20gazing%20at%20me%20sadly%20as%20I%20peeked%20out%20of%20my%20bedroom%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20did%20learn%20good%20money%20management%20from%20my%20parents%2C%20though%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20this%20particular%20childhood%20episode%20may%20have%20hindered%20me%2C%20I%20was%20lucky%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20both%20of%20my%20parents%20were%20hardworking%20people.%20While%20we%20weren't%20wealthy%2C%20my%20three%20siblings%20and%20I%20never%20lacked%20for%20anything.%20My%20parents%20were%20geniuses%20at%20stretching%20dollars%20and%20making%20the%20best%20of%20any%20situation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20allowed%20them%20to%20pursue%20their%20passion%20for%20road%20trips%2C%20first%20by%20stuffing%20all%20six%20of%20us%2C%20our%20luggage%2C%20and%20as%20much%20food%20as%20would%20fit%20in%20the%20Thunderbird%20(I%20always%20ended%20up%20squeezed%20between%20my%20two%20older%20brothers%20with%20my%20mom's%20makeup%20case%20jammed%20under%20my%20feet)%2C%20then%20later%20on%20in%20the%20comparative%20luxury%20of%20a%20small%20camper%20van.%20Whether%20a%20weekend%20outing%20or%20a%20