0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPuppetry%2C%20once%20the%20pride%20of%20Sindhudurg%2C%20had%20assumed%20the%20status%20of%20a%20dying%20art%20form.%20The%20Pinguli%20village%20used%20to%20be%20a%20vibrant%20space%20where%20marionettes%20danced%20to%20tunes%20and%20dialogues%20narrated%20by%20their%20puppeteer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20village%20was%20home%20to%20the%20Thakkar%20Adivasi%20community%20who%20were%20also%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Eparamparik%20kalakars%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(traditional%20artists).%20The%20story%20goes%20that%20the%20community%20received%20patronage%20from%20Chhatrapati%20Shivaji%20who%20granted%20them%20land%20around%20Pinguli%20in%20the%20mid-18th%20century.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20community%20settled%20in%20the%20region%2C%20giving%20up%20their%20nomadic%20lifestyle%20to%20engage%20in%20performance%20crafts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20with%20time%2C%20these%20crafts%20began%20to%20lose%20popularity.%20So%2C%20when%20Sawant%20stumbled%20upon%20the%20village%20while%20scouting%20for%20local%20crafts%20that%20would%20attract%20tourists%2C%20she%20was%20thrilled.%20In%20the%20months%20that%20followed%2C%20she%20set%20up%20the%20puppet%20museum%20%E2%80%98Thakkar%20Adivasi%20Lok%20Kala%20Museum%E2%80%99%20and%20got%20artists%20and%20designers%20on%20board%20to%20do%20a%20skill%20upgrade%20and%20design%20intervention%20workshop.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20intent%20was%20to%20train%20the%20puppeteers%20in%20how%20to%20organise%20the%20shows%20and%20create%20small%20products%20using%20their%20art%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20no%20one%20who%20visits%20Sindhudurg%20goes%20back%20without%20a%20visit%20to%20The%20Pinguli%20Arts%20Complex%20devoted%20to%20reviving%20and%20preserving%20the%20traditional%20crafts.%20On%20display%20are%20traditional%20art%20forms%20including%20%E2%80%98Chitrakathi%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20the%20art%20of%20telling%20stories%20through%20pictures%2C%20%E2%80%98Kal%20Sutli%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%