Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20reasons%20that%20cause%20forest%20fires%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIncidences%20of%20forest%20fires%20are%20common%20between%20February%20and%20mid-July.%20These%20fires%20are%20exacerbated%20largely%20by%20human%20activities%20such%20as%20slash-and-burn%20agriculture%2C%20the%20use%20of%20fire%20for%20land%20clearance%2C%20and%20reckless%20disposal%20of%20lit%20%3Cem%3Ebeedi%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20cigarettes.%20Besides%2C%20there%20is%20also%20a%20myth%20among%20local%20villagers%20that%20if%20they%20set%20the%20forest%20ablaze%2C%20it%20induces%20rain%20that%20will%20yield%20nutritious%20fodder%20for%20livestock.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20fires%20not%20only%20result%20in%20the%20loss%20of%20valuable%20forest%20resources%20and%20wildlife%20but%20also%20affect%20humans%20in%20direct%20and%20indirect%20ways.%20It%20pollutes%20our%20water%20sources%20that%20originate%20from%20forests.%20It%20also%20increases%20their%20risk%20of%20drying%20up.%20Usually%2C%20villagers%20store%20firewood%20and%20fodder%20in%20their%20homes.%20And%20when%20these%20forest%20fires%20reach%20these%20habitations%2C%20they%20take%20a%20dreadful%20form%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20Uttarakhand%20accounts%20for%201.6%20percent%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20geographical%20area.%20But%20in%20terms%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F250621%2Fforest-fires-save-pradeep-mirase-ifs-similipal-malkangiri-environment-biodiversity-hero-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforest%20cover%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20state%20accounts%20for%2045%20percent%20compared%20to%20national%20forest%20cover%20of%20just%2021.67%20percent%20%E2%80%94%20this%20signifies%20the%20rich%20biological%20heritage%20of%20the%20state%20and%20the%20urgency%20to%20save%20one%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20largest%20carbon%20sinks.%3